==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested in 1656.
* From {{etyl|fr}} {{term|abrasion|lang=fr}} (attested since 1611), from {{etyl|ML.}} {{term|abrasio||a scraping|lang=la}}, from {{term|abrado|abrādō|scrape off|lang=la}}
* ''See'' [[abrade#Etymology|abrade]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{ IPA|/ə.ˈbɹeɪ.ʒən/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʒən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[abrading]], wearing, or rubbing off; the wearing away by friction.
# The substance thus rubbed off.
# {{context|medicine}} A [[superficial]] [[excoriation]], with loss of substance under the form of small shreds.
# {{context|geology}} The effect of mechanical [[erosion]] of rock, especially a river bed, by rock fragments scratching and scraping it.

